  "question_id": "f6e2824a-3a72-41cb-afb8-37f9f6bc5cbf",
  "short_text": "Right Angled Triangle",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints a **Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n```\n*\n**\n***\n****\n```\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as a **Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 3`,\n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **3** rows as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/right-angled-triangle.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n*\n**\n***\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "f80f34bb-1a61-43d8-98e7-ae8b5a06cd8c",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\ncounter = 1\n\nwhile counter <= number:\n    print(\"*\" * counter)\n    counter = counter + 1",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
